eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.csv.numerical

Class BPlusTree<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.csv.numerical.BPlusTree<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - Type variable representing the keys of the indexed objects.
    V - Type variable representing the values of the indexed objects.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Index<Object,Object>, Serializable

    public class BPlusTree<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V>
extends Object
implements Index<Object,Object>, Serializable
    Implements a B+-tree index to be used in similarity search against numerical values. This source code adjusts and extends the one available at https://github.com/jiaguofang/b-plus-tree TODO: Implement serialization of the constructed index.

        public List<V> search(K key)
        Returns the value to which the specified key is associated, or null if this tree contains no association for the key.

        A return value of null does not necessarily indicate that the tree contains no association for the key; it's also possible that the tree explicitly associates the key to null.
